  "commentary": "With SPX at 6749.95 trading above the GEX flip at 6703 but surrounded by massive negative gamma walls, dealers are forced to buy this rally as they hedge short gamma positions, creating momentum amplification. The concentration of negative GEX between 6735-6755 (-45M combined) means any move within this zone will be magnified by dealer flow, while the positive gamma wall at 6800 represents strong resistance where dealers will sell into strength. Given the wall_break and gex_surge events with extreme negative readings, expect volatile trending moves with 6703 as the critical flip level and 6800 as the upside target.\n\nBottom line: dealers are buying the move higher but volatility will spike on any direction change.",
